Having just come back from Güzelyurt I have to say that things are looking up. The town center looks healthy, vibrant and giving off strong vibes for business with plenty of new shops opening up. I noticed however many of the old independent traders were struggling to keep their businesses going as eating out is fairly cheap and people the young luxury cars are a classic sign of prosperity so I suppose they have a good excuse to treat themselves. I wish them well as I'm sure the cr*p posts on NL by those hiding behind the name of business partners are never going to do any of these businesses any good.

145 is needed because the market regulation set out will halt current activity so halve is not required.
